1
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:59,480
What a coincidence.

2
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:01,920
Speak of the devil, and he appears.

3
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:04,120
- Who are you calling the devil?
- Usa.

4
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:05,640
Go ahead, then.

5
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:08,560
You hit me, I hit you back. Fair game.

6
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:13,760
Mr. Thee, please wait!

7
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:17,560
This angle's perfect.

8
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:18,880
Let me take a picture for you.

9
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:21,600
One, two, thre…

10
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:34,200
Not me!

11
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:02,120
What?

12
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:03,880
- Are you crazy?!
- What?

13
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:29,240
If you weren't my client,
I would've knocked you cold.

14
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:17,120
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

15
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:19,480
Let's go, honey.

16
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:21,240
Good morning.

17
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:23,840
- Good morning.
- Hm?

18
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:26,720
I can go from here. I'm old enough now.

19
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:29,280
Wow!

20
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,240
Isn't my daughter just the greatest?

21
00:04:31,320 --> 00:04:32,760
Who'd you get it from?

22
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:33,680
Maybe this woman?

23
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:35,240
Fist bump!

24
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:38,160
Let me give you a kiss.

25
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:41,720
Pay attention in class, okay?

26
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:43,960
- See you later.
- See you later. Go on.

27
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:47,040
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye.

28
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:51,720
Aunt Mook!

29
00:04:53,280 --> 00:04:55,920
- Poonpun! Hello.
- Good morning.

30
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:58,160
Your mom drove you today?

31
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,200
Yes.

32
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:00,840
Head inside, Pun.

33
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:03,440
Wait.

34
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:06,560
Did you forget something?

35
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:11,480
- See you later.
- Yes. Go on.

36
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:17,840
Hello, Ms. Prao. You drove Poonpun today?

37
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:23,320
Yes. I should be here more often,

38
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:26,760
or people could start mistaking
others for Poonpun's mom.

39
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:31,160
Are you insinuating something?

40
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:36,360
I just wanted to tell you,

41
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:40,120
you and Pat are just boss and employee.

42
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:42,240
If you act too close,

43
00:05:42,840 --> 00:05:46,480
people might misinterpret that.

44
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:50,560
Well, it depends on the person.

45
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:53,400
If their heart is evil,

46
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:55,240
they can only think evil.

47
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:59,680
But I am aware that Mr. Pat and I
are just boss and employee,

48
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:02,120
so you don't have to worry.

49
00:06:04,960 --> 00:06:07,840
If that's the case, then good.

50
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:15,720
I suggest you spend more time
doing something good for your family

51
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:19,360
rather than listening
to people talking nonsense.

52
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:21,800
If you'll excuse me.

53
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:28,000
Did she just insult us?

54
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,400
PRAO

55
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:41,760
<i>You have to deal with her.</i>

56
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:44,360
She insulted and humiliated me.

57
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:46,880
You had a fight with Mook again, Prao?

58
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:50,200
I just warned her
not to act like Poonpun's mom.

59
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:53,640
She's only befriending our son
because she wants you. How disgusting!

60
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,840
That's ridiculous.

61
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:58,440
She never did that kind of thing.

62
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:01,200
I told you not to let her near our son!

63
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:04,600
If you're calling me just because of this,

64
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:06,880
I don't want to talk. I'm tired of it.

65
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:09,320
I'm giving you an ultimatum.

66
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:12,000
Close your company and come work with Dad.

67
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:14,360
Your company's sinking anyway, isn't it?

68
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:16,320
No one has the right
to tell me to close it.

69
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:17,760
Not even you.

70
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:20,560
I'll prove it to you that we can make it.

71
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:24,440
And stop dragging Mook into this.

72
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:26,080
She's got nothing to do with us.

73
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:28,200
Fine! You'd better keep your word.

74
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:31,280
Your stupid travel agency
is going under eventually.

75
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:34,320
If you can start it, I can end it too!

76
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:47,760
He's really something.

77
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:49,200
Really hot, you mean?

78
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:52,480
Really picky and demanding, more like.

79
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:56,600
Mook, did he like
the special show we prepared?

80
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:58,160
No.

81
00:07:58,840 --> 00:07:59,920
He didn't like it?

82
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,200
Where's the boss, Mr. Sue?

83
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:19,880
It's Suetrong.

84
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:22,680
Sorry.

85
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:24,240
He hasn't arrived yet.

86
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:27,040
This morning he called,
saying he might not come.

87
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:31,160
Mook, you might want to call him.

88
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:33,000
He doesn't sound okay.

89
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:36,039
Sure.

90
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:39,240
What can we call you for short?

91
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:41,360
My father only gave me a full first name.

92
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:45,520
If we can't call you Sue, how about Trong?

93
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:47,000
It's kind of cute.

94
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,920
What should I order for you today?

95
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,880
I'll just go to the dining area.

96
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:24,120
I want to try our hotel's food.

97
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:25,880
Sure.

98
00:09:56,560 --> 00:09:57,480
Hello, Mook.

99
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:01,440
<i>Where are you, Boss? I'm here.</i>

100
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:07,160
Any updates on the background check?

101
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:09,520
On Ms. Mook and Mr. Apichart, correct?

102
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:12,080
Well, those two--

103
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:20,600
Are you alright, Mook?

104
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:24,000
I should be asking you that.

105
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,520
Are you alright?

106
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:27,880
Why are you drinking so early?

107
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:29,080
Hello, Mr. Anapat.

108
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:32,920
Hello, Mr. Thee.

109
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,520
Won't you even say hello?

110
00:10:39,760 --> 00:10:40,880
Ms. Mook.

111
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:50,560
Hello, Mr. Thee.

112
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:54,320
Are you having a meeting?

113
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,560
Oh, no, we're not.

114
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:01,680
I just happened to be in the area,
so I invited her to lunch.

115
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,840
This place is lovely.

116
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,240
Thank you.

117
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:09,360
Since you're both here,

118
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:11,520
would you like to join me for lunch?

119
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:13,320
I don't think we can.

120
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:15,480
We have somewhere to be after this.

121
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:17,600
We're very sorry, Mr. Thee.

122
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:23,280
Is it because you can't, or is it…

123
00:11:26,680 --> 00:11:27,800
We can.

124
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:32,360
It's an honor to have lunch with you.

125
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:33,640
How could we refuse?

126
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:36,080
As for our appointment,

127
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,480
I can postpone it.

128
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:58,280
First of all, I'd like to thank you
for the wonderful tour you presented.

129
00:11:59,160 --> 00:12:00,520
I had a lot of fun.

130
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,360
I hope you're satisfied with our services.

131
00:12:15,240 --> 00:12:16,160
Aren't you drinking?

132
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:21,480
From what I recall, when we first met,

133
00:12:21,560 --> 00:12:22,880
you drank quite a lot.

134
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:28,400
Sure.

135
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:41,520
You seem pretty close to your employee.

136
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:42,920
It must've been a while.

137
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:48,040
Yes, Mook is both my employee
and my best friend.

138
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:53,720
Ms. Mook did a great job.

139
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:56,240
She analyzes her clients well.

140
00:12:56,320 --> 00:13:00,800
It's good that we met today
because I wanted to tell you…

141
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:12,240
There's one more tour
I want her to take me on.

142
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:13,640
What?

143
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:16,640
I'd like to check out Narin Beach Resort.

144
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:19,280
Would that work for you, Mr. Anapat?

145
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:22,200
Um, I…

146
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:25,680
Sure. That should work just fine.

147
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:35,360
I'm looking forward to working
with you, Mr. Anapat.

148
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:37,120
Me too.

149
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:38,680
If you'll excuse me.

150
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:41,880
Please enjoy as much as you'd like.

151
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:42,880
This meal's on me.

152
00:13:48,280 --> 00:13:50,720
- See you tomorrow.
- Tomorrow?

153
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:09,560
Are you sure about this, Mook?

154
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:11,360
We can send someone else.

155
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:16,160
He seems a bit off,
like he intends to mess with you.

156
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,920
<i>Mr. Suetrong, do you know</i>

157
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,440
if Boss has had any problems lately?

158
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:27,600
I'm not sure about his personal matters,

159
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:32,000
but he's probably stressed out
about our company.

160
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:35,680
Ever since COVID,

161
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:38,920
you know how bad our cash flow has been.

162
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:42,840
Yes. Boss told me that too.

163
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:45,040
Recently, we got a call from the bank,

164
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:47,320
saying they won't approve
our new loan yet.

165
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:48,760
Right now,

166
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:52,040
we're spending more than we're earning

167
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:55,240
because many customers
are still unsure about traveling.

168
00:14:57,720 --> 00:15:00,520
Yet, he never let it affect his staff.

169
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:03,960
And the others don't know about this?

170
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:05,680
They don't.

171
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:12,520
Boss told me himself
that we must be sincere with our staff.

172
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:14,800
Our staff work hard,

173
00:15:15,440 --> 00:15:18,480
so we have to be responsible
for every problem.

174
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:27,640
It's fine, Boss. I'll go.

175
00:15:29,040 --> 00:15:30,720
Don't you worry.

176
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:33,280
I'll get us through this crisis.

177
00:15:34,680 --> 00:15:36,480
I'm still worried about you, though.

178
00:15:37,280 --> 00:15:39,360
Especially now that I saw he's still mad--

179
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:41,560
You're acting like you don't know me.

180
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:43,920
What could that man-child ever do to me?

181
00:15:47,160 --> 00:15:48,880
I'll be fine.

182
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:53,120
Plus, if we land this deal, our company
won't have to struggle anymore.

183
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:57,480
You said it yourself.

184
00:15:57,560 --> 00:16:00,480
I'm your employee and best friend.

185
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:03,360
That's why you have to believe in me.

186
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:04,400
Okay?

187
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:20,120
Why are you going to Narin Beach Resort?

188
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:23,440
That's not on the original program.

189
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:28,680
My friend suggested
that it seemed interesting,

190
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:31,520
so I wanted to check it out.

191
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:34,720
It could be an opportunity
to expand our business.

192
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:38,000
Sure.

193
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:40,600
I'll handle the booking.

194
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:42,760
That's alright. I'll do it myself.

195
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:48,680
You don't have to go either,
since Mook will come with me.

196
00:16:50,040 --> 00:16:50,920
Sure.

197
00:16:53,760 --> 00:16:57,400
Family Tour has responded
about the pitch for their program.

198
00:16:58,200 --> 00:17:01,440
I'll schedule it for you once you're back.

199
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:04,480
How are you? Feeling any better?

200
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:09,280
Thank you, Mook.

201
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:12,360
No one knows me better than you do.

202
00:18:14,120 --> 00:18:15,440
That's not true.

203
00:18:15,520 --> 00:18:18,360
I don't even know
what's been bothering you.

204
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:23,320
Is it really that obvious
something's bothering me?

205
00:18:23,920 --> 00:18:25,720
It's so obvious.

206
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:27,240
I just don't know what it is.

207
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:30,960
But let me tell you,
if it's about our company,

208
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:32,640
I'll do my best to help.

209
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:36,600
But if it's a personal matter…

210
00:18:39,080 --> 00:18:40,560
You met Prao, didn't you?

211
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:43,640
Are you okay?

212
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:47,240
If you're not, I apologize on her behalf.

213
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:52,640
I don't understand
why she's so unreasonable either.

214
00:18:52,720 --> 00:18:55,560
Is this what's bothering you?

215
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:02,840
I tried my best to explain things to her,

216
00:19:04,040 --> 00:19:05,520
but she just wouldn't listen.

217
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:08,600
She's misunderstanding us.

218
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:28,520
- Mook.
- Yes?

219
00:19:29,040 --> 00:19:30,560
Can I talk to you?

220
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:36,880
Is something going on between you
and Mr. Pat besides work?

221
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:40,920
Did you hear something about that?

222
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:43,000
Why are you asking me this?

223
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:47,560
The parents at the school
are bad-mouthing you.

224
00:19:48,560 --> 00:19:51,680
I don't want anyone
gossiping about us for fun,

225
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:54,480
and I don't want Kongkwan to hear either.

226
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:59,400
We're just boss and employee, Mom.

227
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:02,640
You once had a family too,

228
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:06,000
and it fell apart because of a mistress.

229
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:09,640
I don't want you to become one yourself.

230
00:20:17,960 --> 00:20:19,400
I'm ready, Mommy.

231
00:20:19,480 --> 00:20:21,560
Good. Say goodbye to Grandma.

232
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:23,520
I'm going to school now, Grandma.

233
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:24,440
See you later.

234
00:20:24,520 --> 00:20:26,120
Pay attention in class, okay?

235
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:28,440
I'll prepare you something delicious.

236
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:29,880
Yes, Grandma.

237
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:33,400
I'm so happy.

238
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:47,600
I think you should try
clearing the air with Ms. Prao

239
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:50,360
before it's too late.

240
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:56,960
I did, Mook,

241
00:20:59,320 --> 00:21:01,160
but it's like we aren't on the same page.

242
00:21:03,280 --> 00:21:06,280
We both believe we're the one who's right.

243
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:10,600
It's so bad that we can't talk at all.

244
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:18,800
The day Kuk had an affair,

245
00:21:21,080 --> 00:21:22,600
I felt like…

246
00:21:24,360 --> 00:21:27,520
I was worthless. I felt invisible.

247
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:34,520
Maybe Ms. Prao's just waiting
for you to go talk to her

248
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:36,840
and clear the air with her.

249
00:21:41,880 --> 00:21:43,240
Honestly, Mook,

250
00:21:44,880 --> 00:21:46,800
I still can't tell

251
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:49,560
if I separated from her

252
00:21:50,280 --> 00:21:52,320
because I don't love her anymore

253
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:55,200
or because I love myself more.

254
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:03,640
Either way, I'll consider
what you suggested.

255
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:41,000
Mr. Thee,
could you help me out with the bags?

256
00:22:41,080 --> 00:22:41,960
Mr. Thee!

257
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:57,160
Good morning. Thank you so much.

258
00:22:57,240 --> 00:22:59,760
Here. Thank you.

259
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:14,880
Mr. Thee.

260
00:23:16,360 --> 00:23:17,360
Are you hungry?

261
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:21,480
I'll order room service for you,
so you can avoid the crowds.

262
00:23:21,560 --> 00:23:22,600
No, thanks.

263
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:24,800
I want to have dinner
with you at the dining area.

264
00:23:26,080 --> 00:23:27,000
What?

265
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:30,800
Is there a problem?

266
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:34,960
Not at all.

267
00:23:36,520 --> 00:23:37,880
I'm curious, though.

268
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:40,000
Why'd you choose this place?

269
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:43,320
This wasn't on the original program.

270
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:48,040
I just wanted to come to the beach,

271
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:52,000
and I didn't want to be alone.

272
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:57,800
Go put your bags away,

273
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:01,200
then let's take a look around the hotel,

274
00:24:02,280 --> 00:24:05,840
in case we get a good idea
we can apply to our hotel.

275
00:24:07,280 --> 00:24:08,960
You mean "your" hotel.

276
00:24:09,040 --> 00:24:10,760
Our hotel is right.

277
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:15,160
If your agency partners with my hotel,

278
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:18,800
it'll be like we're working together,

279
00:24:19,560 --> 00:24:20,840
so what I said was right.

280
00:24:23,120 --> 00:24:24,280
Or…

281
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:28,600
if you want to be more
than just a partner, then sure.

282
00:24:34,280 --> 00:24:36,760
Let me make things clear.

283
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:40,960
I really didn't want to do any of this,

284
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:45,160
but because it's my job, I have no choice.

285
00:24:45,240 --> 00:24:47,120
Still, I'll do my best.

286
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:53,840
Mr. Anapat was right.

287
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:55,400
You're an outstanding employee.

288
00:25:03,080 --> 00:25:05,200
Are you thinking
of investing in this place?

289
00:25:06,160 --> 00:25:09,920
A CEO like you
wouldn't be here just for vacation.

290
00:25:11,160 --> 00:25:16,240
Yes. I must have everything I want,
no matter how hard it is.

291
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:19,880
And once I've done the math,
I rarely ever miss.

292
00:25:23,840 --> 00:25:25,520
Must be nice to be rich.

293
00:25:59,880 --> 00:26:02,240
Why do I have to go to dinner with you?

294
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:05,000
What should I do?

295
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:24,480
Mr. Thee said to give you these.

296
00:26:26,040 --> 00:26:27,120
Thank you.

297
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:07,040
<i>Please dress appropriately.</i>

298
00:27:07,680 --> 00:27:12,000
<i>Show some respect</i>
<i>for the place and for me.</i>

299
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:23,920
For Boss… For the company…

300
00:27:24,760 --> 00:27:27,040
For Boss… For the company…

301
00:27:33,440 --> 00:27:35,240
- This way, please.
- Thank you.

302
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:42,600
Oh.

303
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:49,480
Excuse me.

304
00:27:49,560 --> 00:27:51,880
Excuse me. Sorry.

305
00:27:52,720 --> 00:27:55,320
Here, let me help you.

306
00:27:55,880 --> 00:27:57,000
Thank you.

307
00:27:58,600 --> 00:28:00,160
Want to sit over here?

308
00:28:00,240 --> 00:28:03,160
This way, please.

309
00:28:03,800 --> 00:28:05,040
Thank you.

310
00:28:21,840 --> 00:28:23,680
Not this room. Follow me.

311
00:28:23,760 --> 00:28:24,960
Come on.

312
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:38,440
Kid, are you okay? Are you hurt?

313
00:28:40,840 --> 00:28:42,520
Why'd you stop suddenly?

314
00:28:43,840 --> 00:28:45,000
Are you hurt?

315
00:28:45,080 --> 00:28:46,240
- You're fine, honey.
- You okay?

316
00:28:46,320 --> 00:28:47,240
You're fine.

317
00:28:47,320 --> 00:28:48,840
Thank you.

318
00:28:48,920 --> 00:28:50,360
- You're welcome.
- I appreciate it.

319
00:28:50,440 --> 00:28:51,840
Do you know that woman?

320
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:55,200
- You're alright.
- Thank you.

321
00:28:55,280 --> 00:28:57,520
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

322
00:28:58,440 --> 00:28:59,480
I don't,

323
00:29:01,440 --> 00:29:02,760
but I want to know something.

324
00:29:21,080 --> 00:29:22,400
I'm so sorry.

325
00:29:25,520 --> 00:29:27,080
Have we met before?

326
00:29:28,840 --> 00:29:31,680
No. I've never met you before.

327
00:29:39,800 --> 00:29:40,960
Let's go.

328
00:30:06,200 --> 00:30:07,520
Whoa, hey!

329
00:30:08,600 --> 00:30:11,840
Easy there. You're going
to end up on the floor.

330
00:30:14,600 --> 00:30:15,560
What?

331
00:30:34,080 --> 00:30:34,920
Thank you

332
00:30:38,400 --> 00:30:39,960
for coming with me.

333
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:46,440
Don't thank me.

334
00:30:46,520 --> 00:30:48,360
It's just part of my job.

335
00:30:55,840 --> 00:30:57,440
It must be hard for you,

336
00:31:00,200 --> 00:31:04,240
doing all those things you don't want to…

337
00:31:07,160 --> 00:31:08,400
just for the money.

338
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:13,960
You were born with a silver spoon,

339
00:31:14,680 --> 00:31:16,400
so you never had to struggle.

340
00:31:17,400 --> 00:31:19,840
That's why you don't know
the value of money.

341
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:24,120
I've done my duty today.

342
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:25,840
If you'll excuse me.

343
00:31:26,560 --> 00:31:27,400
How would you know

344
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:30,440
I've never had to struggle?

345
00:31:34,720 --> 00:31:35,720
Mr. Thee!

346
00:31:42,120 --> 00:31:42,960
Hey.

347
00:31:47,880 --> 00:31:48,760
Hey!

348
00:31:50,600 --> 00:31:53,040
Mr. Thee! Hey!

349
00:31:56,960 --> 00:31:59,480
Mr. Thee, are you alright?

350
00:32:10,320 --> 00:32:12,000
Hey! Careful!

351
00:32:14,400 --> 00:32:15,560
You had a little too much to drink.

352
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:17,200
Let's get you to your room.

353
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:20,040
- Come on. Get up.
- Auntie.

354
00:32:21,360 --> 00:32:24,600
Hey. You're calling me an auntie again.

355
00:32:27,360 --> 00:32:29,160
Has anyone ever left you before?

356
00:32:46,440 --> 00:32:47,680
What? Hey!

357
00:33:10,520 --> 00:33:11,960
- Where are we going?
- Come on.

358
00:33:12,640 --> 00:33:14,400
Pull yourself together!

359
00:33:16,240 --> 00:33:18,480
- Here's your key card.
- Thank you.

360
00:33:19,360 --> 00:33:21,720
- Mr. Thee! Come on!
- Where are we going?

361
00:33:21,800 --> 00:33:22,800
‪The bed.

362
00:33:47,480 --> 00:33:49,520
Alright. Stay still.

363
00:33:54,960 --> 00:33:57,080
Other side. Come on.

364
00:34:15,760 --> 00:34:17,719
Hey, let go!

365
00:34:17,800 --> 00:34:18,960
Mr. Thee!

366
00:34:19,040 --> 00:34:23,000
Let go of me! Let go. Hey!

367
00:34:24,560 --> 00:34:26,159
Don't leave me.

368
00:34:28,239 --> 00:34:32,120
Don't leave me. Don't leave me…

369
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:34,600
Mr. Thee. Let go.

370
00:34:37,360 --> 00:34:38,560
Mr. Thee!

371
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:44,920
Mr. Thee. Mr. Thee, wake up! Wake up.

372
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:48,719
Wake up, Mr. Thee!

373
00:34:48,800 --> 00:34:52,480
MOOK

374
00:34:52,560 --> 00:34:54,920
<i>I can't breathe! Mr. Thee!</i>

375
00:34:55,440 --> 00:34:56,520
<i>Get off me!</i>

376
00:35:00,440 --> 00:35:04,560
<i>I'm getting tired. Mr. Thee!</i>

377
00:35:09,160 --> 00:35:11,880
Whan, who's Mook with right now?

378
00:35:11,960 --> 00:35:15,120
She's with Mr. Thee, the CEO of The One.

379
00:35:15,960 --> 00:35:17,640
My dear Mr. Thee!

380
00:35:18,200 --> 00:35:22,000
My dear Mr. Thee! Mook,
how dare you steal my man?

381
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:26,480
Hello, Mook.

382
00:35:26,560 --> 00:35:30,960
Mr. Thee! Let go! Mr. Thee!

383
00:35:34,400 --> 00:35:36,600
Don't hang up, Mook.
We didn't even talk yet.

384
00:35:39,200 --> 00:35:40,840
To achieve victory,

385
00:35:41,360 --> 00:35:44,440
she'd go so far
as to spend the night with him?

386
00:35:45,040 --> 00:35:49,120
What a great manager she is.

387
00:35:52,520 --> 00:35:54,560
Hey, Mr. Thee!

388
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:11,120
Please!

389
00:36:11,200 --> 00:36:12,560
That's all you got?

390
00:37:13,720 --> 00:37:15,000
MOOK

391
00:37:15,080 --> 00:37:17,040
<i>Hello? Hello.</i>

392
00:37:19,200 --> 00:37:21,480
Is this Mook's number?

393
00:37:25,480 --> 00:37:27,160
ANAPAT

394
00:37:42,640 --> 00:37:45,200
I think so, Mr. Anapat.

395
00:37:45,280 --> 00:37:46,200
<i>Mr. Thee.</i>

396
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:49,200
Where is she?

397
00:37:49,880 --> 00:37:52,040
<i>Why do you have her phone?</i>

398
00:38:00,720 --> 00:38:01,600
Mr. Thee!

399
00:38:03,160 --> 00:38:04,880
Hey! Careful!

400
00:38:06,160 --> 00:38:07,440
You had a little too much to drink.

401
00:38:07,520 --> 00:38:09,600
Has anyone ever left you before?

402
00:38:14,320 --> 00:38:16,640
Um, I…

403
00:38:16,720 --> 00:38:19,680
<i>She was with me last night, and…</i>

404
00:38:20,480 --> 00:38:22,560
I'm sorry? Mr. Thee.

405
00:38:33,600 --> 00:38:36,640
Hello, Mr. Thee. Mr. Thee?

406
00:39:07,080 --> 00:39:08,120
Is there something urgent?

407
00:39:08,200 --> 00:39:09,320
I'm looking for something.

408
00:39:11,680 --> 00:39:14,280
What? Why do you have it?

409
00:39:17,560 --> 00:39:19,000
Hey! Hold it!

410
00:39:19,080 --> 00:39:21,440
Come on, to the restroom.

411
00:39:21,520 --> 00:39:23,680
Quick! Hold it in! Let's go.

412
00:39:25,200 --> 00:39:26,040
Hold it in.

413
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:29,400
Okay, now go.

414
00:39:40,480 --> 00:39:42,360
Are you okay?

415
00:39:45,560 --> 00:39:46,640
‪You okay?

416
00:40:04,200 --> 00:40:06,760
Could you… take off your shirt?

417
00:40:32,720 --> 00:40:33,960
Hey,

418
00:40:35,720 --> 00:40:37,240
wipe the drool off your face, Auntie.

419
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:44,720
You could've just unbuttoned it.

420
00:40:44,800 --> 00:40:46,000
Why'd you take it off?

421
00:40:46,080 --> 00:40:48,440
Well, you told me to take off my shirt.

422
00:41:22,120 --> 00:41:23,880
Having dirty thoughts about me?

423
00:41:27,960 --> 00:41:30,040
I'm not! Are you crazy?

424
00:41:31,600 --> 00:41:34,160
I'm done. You can go back
to your room now.

425
00:41:34,240 --> 00:41:35,240
I'm packing up.

426
00:41:40,800 --> 00:41:42,080
What's wrong with you?

427
00:41:42,160 --> 00:41:43,520
You didn't even wipe much.

428
00:41:47,160 --> 00:41:48,360
I'll meet you in the lobby.

429
00:42:16,560 --> 00:42:18,360
There you go.

430
00:42:18,440 --> 00:42:20,120
Thank you. Come on.

431
00:42:24,680 --> 00:42:26,840
- Isn't it lovely?
- It really is!

432
00:42:26,920 --> 00:42:27,840
So beautiful.

433
00:42:27,920 --> 00:42:28,800
Ms. Prao sure is sweet.

434
00:42:28,880 --> 00:42:31,600
She gave us a voucher for the hotel,

435
00:42:31,680 --> 00:42:33,440
and she even rented a car for us.

436
00:42:35,080 --> 00:42:35,920
- Let's go.
- Come on.

437
00:42:36,640 --> 00:42:37,480
Let's go.

438
00:42:40,640 --> 00:42:43,360
Thank you.

439
00:42:43,440 --> 00:42:45,480
Mr. Thee, we're all set.

440
00:42:46,320 --> 00:42:47,160
Let's go.

441
00:42:47,240 --> 00:42:49,040
Wait, hold on.

442
00:42:49,120 --> 00:42:50,400
What now?

443
00:42:51,920 --> 00:42:53,880
- Hey, it's okay!
- It's okay.

444
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:56,760
It's to thank you for taking care of me.

445
00:43:09,640 --> 00:43:12,280
Isn't that Mook, Kongkwan's mom?

446
00:43:13,440 --> 00:43:16,600
You're right. Who is she with?

447
00:43:16,680 --> 00:43:18,040
He's tying her shoes, too.

448
00:43:20,520 --> 00:43:21,360
Thank you.

449
00:43:24,360 --> 00:43:26,920
Ms. Mook! What a coincidence.

450
00:43:29,680 --> 00:43:31,760
Hello. Are you here on vacation?

451
00:43:31,840 --> 00:43:35,760
Yes. Are you here on vacation too?

452
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:40,080
What about Kongkwan, though?

453
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:43,640
She didn't come. I'm here for work.

454
00:43:44,240 --> 00:43:45,520
Your work sure looks easy.

455
00:43:45,600 --> 00:43:48,040
It's as if you're on vacation.

456
00:43:49,320 --> 00:43:52,720
She's right. I wish I had your job.

457
00:43:54,200 --> 00:43:57,560
And… aren't you going
to introduce him to us?

458
00:43:59,760 --> 00:44:02,840
This is Mr. Theechuda,
the CEO of TJ Group.

459
00:44:06,400 --> 00:44:08,320
I'd better get going.

460
00:44:08,400 --> 00:44:09,920
Have a great vacation.

461
00:44:10,800 --> 00:44:11,840
Mook.

462
00:44:12,720 --> 00:44:14,160
Boss? Boss--

463
00:44:15,120 --> 00:44:16,160
What?

464
00:44:16,240 --> 00:44:17,080
Boss!

465
00:44:18,320 --> 00:44:19,720
How could you do this?

466
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:20,960
You're not a gentleman!

467
00:44:21,040 --> 00:44:22,320
What are you talking about?

468
00:44:22,400 --> 00:44:23,440
I don't get it.

469
00:44:24,120 --> 00:44:26,440
- Mook, come with me.
- No way!

470
00:44:27,360 --> 00:44:30,040
She came with me, so she leaves with me.

471
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:31,440
Her job isn't done yet.

472
00:44:32,920 --> 00:44:34,600
Hey! Boss.

473
00:44:36,120 --> 00:44:38,040
Mr. Pat, is something wrong?

474
00:44:38,120 --> 00:44:40,560
It's nothing. Please excuse me.

475
00:44:50,000 --> 00:44:54,240
I don't know what happened,
but I apologize on his behalf.

476
00:44:54,320 --> 00:44:55,920
He's never been this way before.

477
00:44:57,120 --> 00:45:01,440
He's probably really worried about you,
maybe even a little too much.

478
00:45:02,960 --> 00:45:04,240
What do you mean?

479
00:45:04,320 --> 00:45:08,520
Well, this morning he called you,
and I picked up the phone,

480
00:45:09,160 --> 00:45:11,000
so I told him you were with me last night.

481
00:45:12,640 --> 00:45:13,880
And then he showed up.

482
00:45:13,960 --> 00:45:17,080
What? Why'd you tell him that?

483
00:45:17,160 --> 00:45:18,720
I was just telling the truth.

484
00:45:19,720 --> 00:45:23,960
I don't know when you left my room,
and your phone fell on my bed.

485
00:45:29,480 --> 00:45:33,120
But you're not mad at him, right?

486
00:45:34,000 --> 00:45:35,480
For punching you in the mouth?

487
00:45:52,520 --> 00:45:53,440
Mook!

488
00:45:54,280 --> 00:45:55,800
Mook, Mook, Mook!

489
00:45:55,880 --> 00:45:57,160
Did you have fun last night?

490
00:45:58,000 --> 00:46:00,200
- Where's our boss? Is he here yet?
- Mook.

491
00:46:02,040 --> 00:46:03,920
What did Mr. Thee do to you? Tell me.

492
00:46:04,520 --> 00:46:05,800
I'll handle him myself.

493
00:46:06,440 --> 00:46:07,640
This isn't about work anymore.

494
00:46:07,720 --> 00:46:11,200
Yes! He can't use work
as an excuse to toy with her like this.

495
00:46:11,280 --> 00:46:12,640
Wait, wait!

496
00:46:12,720 --> 00:46:14,680
You guys misunderstood him.

497
00:46:15,320 --> 00:46:17,200
I heard everything last night.
You and he--

498
00:46:17,280 --> 00:46:19,560
Let me explain first, okay?

499
00:46:27,320 --> 00:46:28,320
That's it?

500
00:46:29,320 --> 00:46:30,680
That is it.

501
00:46:30,760 --> 00:46:34,960
He was so drunk,
so I had to carry him back to his room.

502
00:46:35,040 --> 00:46:37,480
My phone fell,
so I probably dialed you by accident.

503
00:46:38,760 --> 00:46:41,720
If that's true, then I still have a shot.

504
00:46:45,600 --> 00:46:47,000
What are we going to do now, Boss?

505
00:46:47,880 --> 00:46:50,920
Looks like it's over for our company now.

506
00:46:55,720 --> 00:46:58,560
Well, the situation was very misleading.

507
00:46:59,240 --> 00:47:00,360
Don't you all think so?

508
00:47:01,160 --> 00:47:03,680
Boss, how could you think that?

509
00:47:03,760 --> 00:47:06,040
You think I'd sleep with him
for our company?

510
00:47:09,400 --> 00:47:13,480
Guys, I don't think we should be fighting.

511
00:47:13,560 --> 00:47:15,280
Instead, we should be thinking.

512
00:47:15,360 --> 00:47:18,960
If Mr. Thee gets so angry
that he won't partner with us,

513
00:47:19,040 --> 00:47:20,000
how will we survive?

514
00:47:20,080 --> 00:47:23,360
Because I…

515
00:47:23,440 --> 00:47:25,480
I still have a mortgage and car loans.

516
00:47:25,560 --> 00:47:27,960
If you can't handle it,
just let the bank take them.

517
00:47:28,040 --> 00:47:29,800
Why would I do that, Mr. Susan?!

518
00:47:29,880 --> 00:47:31,560
My name's not Susan. It's Suetrong.

519
00:47:32,880 --> 00:47:36,560
If that's the case,
it'll be sadder than not getting the guy.

520
00:47:36,640 --> 00:47:40,240
But May! I've only worked here
for a few years.

521
00:47:40,320 --> 00:47:42,560
I don't want to be unemployed yet!

522
00:47:47,880 --> 00:47:49,360
I'll go talk to Mr. Thee.

523
00:47:49,440 --> 00:47:52,640
You shouldn't. Things will only escalate.

524
00:47:52,720 --> 00:47:54,840
Let me handle this.

525
00:48:22,160 --> 00:48:24,120
Having dirty thoughts about me?

526
00:48:26,840 --> 00:48:28,800
I'm not! Are you crazy?

527
00:48:33,000 --> 00:48:35,080
YOU HAVE A NEW EMAIL

528
00:48:54,400 --> 00:48:56,600
LIABILITIES: 32%

529
00:49:01,200 --> 00:49:02,080
Mr. Thee,

530
00:49:05,280 --> 00:49:08,680
you're going on a trip with Family Tour
tomorrow. Here's the program.

531
00:49:12,480 --> 00:49:16,680
Also, Ms. Mook wanted to see you.

532
00:49:16,760 --> 00:49:18,440
She said she wanted to speak to you.

533
00:49:20,760 --> 00:49:22,240
Don't confirm with her yet.

534
00:49:22,320 --> 00:49:25,160
Please tell her I'll contact her later.

535
00:49:25,240 --> 00:49:26,600
Sure.

536
00:49:30,880 --> 00:49:32,200
Mr. Thee,

537
00:49:33,520 --> 00:49:35,640
I've looked into Ms. Mook like you asked,

538
00:49:36,480 --> 00:49:39,080
and there's one thing
I forgot to tell you.

539
00:49:43,520 --> 00:49:46,680
Okay, Mr. Pitak. I really appreciate it.

540
00:49:48,400 --> 00:49:49,280
Okay.

541
00:50:03,400 --> 00:50:05,520
<i>Has anyone ever left you before?</i>

542
00:50:09,880 --> 00:50:11,240
What? Hey!

543
00:50:25,720 --> 00:50:26,560
Hey!

544
00:50:28,360 --> 00:50:29,960
Don't leave me.

545
00:50:32,040 --> 00:50:33,680
Don't leave me.

546
00:50:35,040 --> 00:50:35,880
Don't leave me…

547
00:50:59,280 --> 00:51:01,760
Usa, when's Mr. Thee going to be here?

548
00:51:02,880 --> 00:51:04,680
Any minute now.

549
00:51:04,760 --> 00:51:05,600
WELCOMING CEREMONY

550
00:51:11,840 --> 00:51:13,400
They really had to do all this?

551
00:51:30,440 --> 00:51:31,640
Good morning.

552
00:51:31,720 --> 00:51:34,720
Family Tour and Travel
would like to welcome you, Mr. Thee.

553
00:51:34,800 --> 00:51:36,040
This way, please.

554
00:51:36,120 --> 00:51:37,120
Please.

555
00:51:38,240 --> 00:51:39,760
This way, please.

556
00:51:42,360 --> 00:51:43,440
This way.

557
00:52:28,040 --> 00:52:29,880
Please have a bite, Mr. Thee.

558
00:52:29,960 --> 00:52:33,280
I had them specially made
just for you. Here.

559
00:53:24,040 --> 00:53:25,880
Would you like to have a bite?

560
00:53:34,960 --> 00:53:35,960
Where are you going?

561
00:53:57,720 --> 00:53:59,520
INCOMING CALL

562
00:54:00,120 --> 00:54:01,840
Hello, Mook speaking.

563
00:54:01,920 --> 00:54:02,960
<i>Come pick me up now.</i>

564
00:54:04,320 --> 00:54:05,200
Mr. Thee?

565
00:54:05,800 --> 00:54:07,320
I'm at Khlong Bang Luang.

566
00:54:07,400 --> 00:54:08,560
I'll give you one hour,

567
00:54:08,640 --> 00:54:10,640
<i>if you still want a shot at winning this.</i>

568
00:54:22,320 --> 00:54:23,360
And… the end!

569
00:54:32,040 --> 00:54:34,400
Where's Mr. Thee? He didn't give us
an interview you promised.

570
00:54:36,280 --> 00:54:38,240
Please calm down, everyone.

571
00:54:38,320 --> 00:54:40,760
I promise you'll get
to interview him today.

572
00:54:40,840 --> 00:54:42,240
Alright?

573
00:54:42,320 --> 00:54:47,040
No one other than Family Tour and Travel
can give you this opportunity.

574
00:54:48,000 --> 00:54:51,320
Why don't you all have a coffee break?

575
00:54:51,400 --> 00:54:54,960
Then, I'll invite him to give you
a proper interview for sure.

576
00:54:55,040 --> 00:54:56,600
Okay? My team will handle it for you.

577
00:54:56,680 --> 00:54:58,880
- Please enjoy.
- We have some snacks for you here.

578
00:54:58,960 --> 00:55:00,200
Please enjoy.

579
00:55:01,400 --> 00:55:02,320
Enjoy.

580
00:55:07,280 --> 00:55:09,120
- Where did he go?
- What?

581
00:55:09,200 --> 00:55:11,000
How should I know?

582
00:55:11,080 --> 00:55:12,520
I've been with you the whole time.

583
00:55:13,760 --> 00:55:15,880
Well, go find him then. Hurry!

584
00:55:33,480 --> 00:55:35,960
THEECHUDA TEERASU
CEO OF THE TOP-TIER HOTEL, THE ONE HOTEL

585
00:55:50,280 --> 00:55:51,600
What's this event?

586
00:55:52,600 --> 00:55:53,960
I probably came to the wrong event.

587
00:55:54,040 --> 00:55:54,920
Let's just go.

588
00:55:55,600 --> 00:55:56,840
To where?

589
00:55:57,560 --> 00:55:59,120
Anywhere but here.

590
00:56:02,400 --> 00:56:03,480
Hurry up and drive.

591
00:56:11,920 --> 00:56:14,480
Mook? You'll regret this.

592
00:56:19,600 --> 00:56:21,880
Come on, Mr. Thee.

593
00:56:21,960 --> 00:56:23,480
Don't leave me like that.

594
00:56:32,080 --> 00:56:34,760
…that your mom's a bad person.

595
00:56:34,840 --> 00:56:36,880
She's dating many guys at once.

596
00:56:38,600 --> 00:56:39,800
Kongkwan, don't!

597
00:56:39,880 --> 00:56:41,120
Did you just push me?!

598
00:56:41,200 --> 00:56:42,960
- Satang, calm down!
- Satang, Satang!

599
00:56:43,040 --> 00:56:44,760
- Satang!
- Everyone, stop it!

600
00:56:45,360 --> 00:56:47,080
…and what I experienced only.

601
00:56:50,120 --> 00:56:54,120
And the company that gets
to sign a contract with us is…

602
00:56:55,720 --> 00:56:57,520
Mook and I aren't what you think we are!

603
00:57:02,640 --> 00:57:03,480
Then what's this?

604
00:57:56,640 --> 00:57:58,880
